Morneau Shepell is Canada’s only consulting and outsourcing company that takes an integrative approach to health, benefits, retirement and employee assistance needs. We apply the expertise of our entire organization to develop innovative answers; be part of our team – working with other experts and professionals to listen and work together to deliver integrative solutions that fit.





Learning and Career Development
We believe it’s important for employees to take an active role in managing their career by:
Having regular discussions with their managers on career goals, professional development, and job satisfaction
Creating a personalized career development path
Participating in their respective industry training programs, such as those leading to actuarial, securities, and Certified Employee Benefits Specialist (CEBS) designations
Taking advantage of Morneau Shepell’s Learning Academy, which offers a wide selection of learning and development opportunities,  tools and resources to help employees excel at their job and  realize their highest potential
Having the opportunity to work on diverse and challenging projects
Generation Flex
Our Generation Flex program can meet the unique needs of our employees and their family members. Employees can take advantage of:
Benefits
Customizable Medical and Dental Plans
Health Spending Accounts
Best Doctors
Confidential personal assistance through our Employee and Family Assistance Program (EFAP)
Health Risk Assessment
Echo Program – proactive information, sent directly to employees, for key life stages
Vacation entitlement beginning at 15 days for all employees
Personal floater days
Summer social events and holiday parties
Financial Security & Retirement
Life and Accident Insurance
Critical Illness Insurance
Short- and Long-Term Disability Coverage
Defined Contribution (DC) Pension plan that includes matching employer contributions
Group Registered Retirement Savings Plan (RRSP) and Group Tax-Free Savings Account (TFSA)
Employee Share Purchase Plan which offers a discounted share price
Value and Reward
Morneau Shepell is committed to the principles of employment equity. We respect, value, and encourage individuality and cultural diversity. Valuing employees is part of our core values and guiding principles. 
We support an Employee Referral Program that offers employees a further opportunity to contribute to the long-term success of the organization, and to be generously rewarded for their efforts.
Accessibility
We encourage applications from all qualified candidates and will accommodate applicants’ needs under applicable human rights and equal opportunity legislation throughout the recruitment and selection process. Please advise the Recruiter to ensure your accessibility needs are accommodated. Information received relating to accommodation will be addressed confidentially.
Check out Morneau Shepell’s career opportunities, visit our LinkedIn page, and follow us on Twitter.





